multiply

public static void multiply(double[][] srcMatrix,
                            double[] srcVector,
                            double[] destination,
                            int n)
Multiplies srcMatrix (n n) with srcVector (length n) and puts the results into destination (length n), i.e. 
 destination = srcMatrix * srcVector
Note that this method does no checks (null or length) for performance reasons and needs no extra memory.

Parameters:
srcMatrix - the source quadratic matrix of size n * n.
srcVector - the source vector of length n.
destination - the destination vector of length n.
n - the size of the arrays to be multiplied.

multiplyExtended

public static void multiplyExtended(double[][] srcMatrixExt,
                                    double[] srcVector,
                                    double[] destination,
                                    int n)
Multiplies the extended srcMatrixExt (n+1* n+1) with srcVector (length n), adds the translational component and puts the results into destination (length n), i.e. 
 destination  = srcMatrixExt * srcVector
 destination += srcMatrixExt[lastColumn]
Note that this method does no checks (null or length) for performance reasons and needs no extra memory.

Parameters:
srcMatrixExt - the extended source quadratic matrix of size n+1 * n+1.
srcVector - the source vector of length n.
destination - the destination vector of length n.
n - the size of the arrays to be multiplied.

multiply

public static void multiply(double[][] srcA,
                            double[][] srcB,
                            double[][] destination,
                            int n)
Multiplies the quadratic matrix srcA with the quadratic matrix srcB and puts the results into destination, i.e. 
 destination = srcA * srcB
Note that this method does no checks (null or length) for performance reasons and needs no extra memory.

Parameters:
srcA - the first quadratic source matrix of size n * n.
srcB - the second quadratic source matrix of size n * n.
destination - the quadratic destination matrix of size n * n.
n - the size of the arrays to be multiplied.

arrayEquals

public static boolean arrayEquals(double[] arr1,
                                  double[] arr2)
Faster implementation of the equals method for two double arrays.

This method is used to avoid multiple activity-, matching- or prediction-calculations.

Note that this method does no length checks for performance reasons.

Parameters:
arr1 - the first array.
arr2 - the second array.
Returns:
true, if the arrays contain the same values.
See Also:
Arrays.equals(double[] a, double[] a2), ConditionHyperellipsoid.getActivity(double[]), RLSPrediction.predict(double[] predInput)

putNumFirstObjectsFirst

public static int putNumFirstObjectsFirst(double[] votes,
                                          int[] nums,
                                          java.lang.Object[] objs,
                                          int size,
                                          int num)
Determines the num first objects, where an object may contain multiple copies specified in nums. Routine determines at least the num first entries, if the entry at the boundary contains more than 1 (specified in nums), it will still be included.

Parameters:
votes - The sorting criterion (largest first)
nums - The number of entries each entry represents.
objs - The objects sorting according to the criteria
size - The number of actual entries in the arrays.
num - The numer of largest objects put to the front
Returns:
The number of first entries that make up the num largest entries.
